# 📄 Employee.java

Contains the POJO class with:

- Employee ID
- Name
- Salary

along with getters and setters.
--> package com.example.demo;

import org.springframework.context.ApplicationContext;

import org.springframework.context.support.ClassPathXmlApplicationContext;

public class Demo {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		ApplicationContext ac = new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext("applicationContext.xml");
		Employee e = (Employee) ac.getBean("emp");
		
		System.out.println("Employee id is" + e.getEmpid());
		System.out.println("Employee name is" + e.getName());
		System.out.println("Employee salary is" + e.getSalary());
	}
}

---

# 📄 applicationContext.xml

Defines the Spring Bean.

```xml
<bean id="emp" class="com.example.demo.Employee">

    <property name="empid" value="101"/>

    <property name="name" value="Ravi"/>

    <property name="salary" value="1000.00"/>

</bean>
```

